      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-a" mid="75" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="44"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>The evil <FONT color=#a82424>Broken Goldstone Thieves</FONT> are terrorizing nearby areas ever since they raided the Goldstone Mine and made it their base. By right, the rightful owner of the <FONT color=#a82424>Broken Goldstone Canyon</FONT> are the <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-b" mid="77" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="45"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>The <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT> live on goldstone so skirmishes often erupted when another tribe thoughtlessly tried to take over the Goldstone Mine. That's why the past Presidents of Merca have signed a deal with the Alicantos and promised to extract only a handful amount of the goldstones.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-c" mid="78" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="46"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>As long as the deal was abided, the <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT> didn't disrupt our goldstone mining, and the Presidents were cautious about keeping a tight control on the sales of the hallucinogenic <FONT color=#a82424>Goldstone Tears</FONT> so they didn't object to mining the goldstone in small amounts.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-d" mid="79" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="47"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>However, when the <FONT color=#a82424>thieves</FONT> started to infiltrate the canyon, an era of suffering began for the <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT>. The thieves chased the Alicantos out and took over the mines for themselves.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-e" mid="80" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="48"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>What's worse is that there are rumours of enslaved <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT> at the core of the <FONT color=#a82424>Broken Goldstone Canyon</FONT> who are being forced into labour.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-f" mid="81" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="49"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>When I was a kid, I followed my father to the Broken Goldstone Canyon and almost got killed by a thief. Luckily, the kind-hearted <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT> saved my life.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-g" mid="83" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Why don't you ask for Vernicka's help?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="50"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>So I was wondering if I could help the <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT> in any way. I want to help them, but I'm only a merchant who doesn't even know how to hold a sword properly. I'm at my wit's end.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-h" mid="84" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(That's likely of Vernicka…)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="51"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>The thieves have grown too large and <FONT color=#a82424>President Vernicka</FONT> is reluctant on countering them directly. I'm sure he must have his own reasons, but it's hard to say that he's interested in freeing the enslaved <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT>…</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-i" mid="86" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>So he's trying to borrow a Child's help.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="52"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>It would be best if the <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT> can escape on their own, but I heard that the leader of the Alicantos who has putting up a strong fight against the thieves has gone over to <FONT color=#a82424>Tryan's Territory</FONT> to become a <FONT color=#a82424>Soldier of Destruction</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-j" mid="87" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Pero is such a good man in Mistland.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="53"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>However, it is impossible to expect much compassion from the <FONT color=#a82424>Goddess Faction</FONT>. I'm sure he'll only be made use of or be ignored. I only hope for his safe return. That would give some hope to the other <FONT color=#a82424>Alicantos</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-j" image="QW_109.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-k" mid="88" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>That's easy.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="54"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>So I was thinking if you could help me. Can you sneak into <FONT color=#a82424>Tryan's Territory</FONT> and see if the Alicanto leader has really joined the Army of Destruction?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-2" mid="90" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="55"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Thank you! I'll think of a way to persuade him to go back if he's really there.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-2" image="QW_109.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="56"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR><FONT color=#a82424>Tryan's Territory</FONT> is a dangerous place so do take extra caution. All you have to do is to check if the leader of the Alicantos is there.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-a" mid="93" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Tell him he wasn't there.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="57"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Did you see Alicanto leader there?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-b" mid="94" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="58"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>It would be a relief if he didn't join the Army of Destruction, but I fear that he might have left this place due to other worse circumstances.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-c" mid="95" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="59"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Anyway, thank you for your help. You must really be a skilled fighter to have come back from such a dangerous place unscathed.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
